1.225(Summary)A
23 508 :M
f1_9 sf
1.894 .189(The pseudo-prototypes for the builtin operators do not work very well for their intended purpose, namely)J
23 520 :M
1.508 .151(overload resolution when considering the use of operator conversion functions on operands of class type.)J
23 532 :M
1.744 .174(The alternative requires a compatible modification to the overloading rules which is useful by itself, plus a)J
23 544 :M
1.686 .169(simplification of the list of pseudo-prototypes which makes them more closely model the behavior of the)J
23 556 :M
2.689 .269(builtin operators themselves.)J
23 580 :M
1.393 .139(These changes make numeric classes much more practical; they explain the behavior of the builtin)J
23 592 :M
1.721 .172(operators using a simple and natural set of prototypes together with the overloading rules exactly as)J
23 604 :M
2.034 .203(applied to ordinary functions; and they greatly reduce certain surprising ambiguities.)J
23 628 :M
1.159 .116(Little if any existing code would be broken by these changes, but future numeric code would be made much)J
23 640 :M
1.732 .173(cleaner and simpler.)J
